<subSubSection id="1C1F5D21D816BED925A41B2D618C6FAC" pageId="131" pageNumber="132" type="description">
<paragraph id="735C3AFF306A38C976781F6929F843E0" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="27CF3FF1C9C97875195FB9E55B653F88" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">
Undershrub to 60 cm, branches fastigiate, sharply spinescent, sericeous when young but later glabrescent. Leaves subsessile, 4-12 
<normalizedToken id="CEC6ACC89760F25D9A30A168E24E7432" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-1.5 mm, acute, entire, cuneate at the base, silvery pubescent. Flowers solitary, axillary, subsessile; peduncles absent; bracteoles 2-3 
<normalizedToken id="2302EC9C3DCCD514C11F373CB0F8B618" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5 mm, oblong, acute; pedicels c. 1 mm; outer sepals 6 
<normalizedToken id="0A4C2442970520609F041E59738B16C4" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3 mm, ovate to elliptic, acute, pubescent on the margins; inner sepals c. 4 mm wide, subrhomboid with hyaline margins; corolla 10-11 mm long, white, midpetaline bands pubescent; filaments glandular basally; ovary glabrous, style glabrous, divided c. 8 mm above base; style arms 0 and 0.5 mm, unequal, stigmas subglobose. Capsule and seeds not known.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="93B7BD66F4499C723F838B696AFA88ED" pageId="131" pageNumber="132" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="F967B8C6083E0B4F16B0FBC3282A0643" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="38A65C3C4FA26A5C7A875602E26F3098" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">
